<paragraph id="IFRS17_B3" base="F55667069"><paranum>B3</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IFRSÂ 17"/><data name="paranum" value="B3"/></prolog><body><p id="IFRS17_P0574">Uncertainty (or risk) is the essence of an <xref base="F55666957" href="IFRS17_APPA.dita#IFRS17_APPA/IFRS17_P0532">insurance contract<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0186"/></ph></xref>. Accordingly, at least one of the following is uncertain at the inception of an insurance contract: </p><ol id="IFRS17_L0102" base="F55667071" type="lower-alpha"><li><li_value>(a)</li_value> <p id="IFRS17_P0575" base="F55667072">the probability of an <xref base="F55666980" href="IFRS17_APPA.dita#IFRS17_APPA/IFRS17_P0541">insured event<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0191"/></ph></xref> occurring;</p></li><li><li_value>(b)</li_value> <p id="IFRS17_P0576" base="F55667074">when the insured event will occur; or</p></li><li><li_value>(c)</li_value> <p id="IFRS17_P0577" base="F55667076">how much the entity will need to pay if the insured event occurs.</p></li></ol></body></paragraph>